:HELP NAME=STREMGEN.Route Maintenance - Help
:XH3.Route Maintenance
:ISCH ROOTS='Route Maintenance'.
Work with Mail Extentions

:P.
The Route Maintenance function enables you to work with mail
extentions. Each entity presents an user or a group who will
get an e-mail.

:P.
You can set the options so that the appropriate user or group
will get the e-mail.

:P.
Users with the selected support level are allowed to start this
function.

:EHELP.

.*   .............................................................   *.
.*   : General Help For Display 1.1                              :   *.
.*   .............................................................   *.

:HELP NAME=OMH055C1.General Help For Display 1-1

:XH3.Display 1-1 - Work with Mail Extentions

:P.
:LINK PERFORM='DSPHELP STREM'.
General Information.
:ELINK.

:P.
The work with Mail Extentions shows a list of all Users who
will get an e-mail when a route changes to the selected route.

:P.
The attributes in this list are:
:PARML.

:PT.User
:PD.
These are the users who will receive an e-mail when the route of the
incident changes.

:PT.Status
:PD.
This is the status of the helpdesk employee. Select one of the
following;
:PT.0=Normal
:PD.
This value indicates that this person is an active helpdesk employee.
:PT.9=Disabled
:PD.
This value indicates that this employee is no longer used for this
helpdesk. A disabled helpdesk employee will be in the database but is
no longer able to add incidents.

:PT.Entry or Exit
:PD.
The entry or exit value indicates when the specific e-mail must be
sent. Select one of the following;
:PT.0=Entry
:PD.
The e-mail is sent when the incident is changed to the statusroute.
:PT.1=Exit
:PD.
The e-mail is sent when the incident is placed into another
statusroute.

:PT.Template File
:PD.
This is the name of the file which contains the mail templates.

:PT.Template Library
:PD.
This is the library of the file which contains the mail templates.

:PT.Template Member
:PD.
This is the name of the member that is used as text for the e-mail.

:EPARML.

